cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses various techniques to improve the performance of the face detector, which suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pretraining on the MS COCO dataset, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses false positives and location accuracy, which are related to computer security, suggesting that it may also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
